<h2>How to Install the Bookmarklets</h2>

<p>Bookmarklets are like browser extensions, but more primitive.</p>

<p>Installation depends on your browser; basically, do whatever it takes to create a bookmark whose "location" field is that long nasty <code>javascript:</code> URL. Some notable approaches:</p>

<h3>In Most Desktop Browsers</h3>

<p>You usually want these on the toolbar so they're easily accessible, but you could also put them in the menu.</p>

<ol>
<li>Go into the "view" menu and make sure the "bookmark toolbar" is visible, or else open your browser's bookmark manager.</li>
<li>Drag the bookmarklet links and drop them where you want them.</li>
</ol>

<h3>On iOS Safari</h3>

<p>You usually want these at the top of the "favorites" section of your bookmarks. That way, you can activate them by tapping on the URL bar and then choosing from the set of big tiles. To install each bookmarklet:</p>

<ol>
<li>First, use the share menu to bookmark some random page, like this one. Put it in the "favorites" section.</li>
<li>Copy the <code>javascript:</code> URL to the clipboard. (On iOS ≥ 13 you can tap-and-hold the links; on iOS ≤ 12 you have to copy from the textarea.)</li>
<li>Open your bookmarks and tap the "edit" button.</li>
<li>Tap the bookmark you just made. Rename it, and replace the current URL with the <code>javascript:</code> URL.</li>
</ol>
